            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Immunity to Magic",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "A viridium golem is immune to any spell or spell-like ability that allows spell resistance. Certain spells and effects function as noted below. <ul> <li>\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 A <i>heal</i> spell deals 5 points of damage per caster level to a viridium golem, to a maximum of 75 points of damage. This damage bypasses the golem\u2019s damage reduction.</li> <li>\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 A <i>remove disease</i> spell staggers a viridium golem for 1 round (no save).</li> </ul>"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Shield",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "A viridium golem\u2019s shield is part of its body and does not provide a bonus to its AC; it functions as a primary natural attack that deals bludgeoning damage. A creature struck by the golem\u2019s shield is exposed to the golem\u2019s disease and must also attempt a DC 24 Fortitude save to avoid being stunned for 1 round. The save DC is Constitution-based. "
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Sword",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "A viridium golem\u2019s sword functions as a primary natural attack that deals slashing damage and can cause both disease and deep, bleeding wounds."
